main event: A Duty Officer reported seeing a brilliant white, triangular shaped object that looked like an aircraft over Wilmington, Ohio.
interesting points: The sighting occurred around 10:15 AM on June 13, 1959, with the object visible for approximately one minute., The object's description noted it appeared solid, bright with a halo, and hovered before moving rapidly out of sight., The witness reported that the object seemed six times larger than a star., There's a mention of a note at the bottom of the document stating 'BROWN,' which is unexplained., The report is part of Project Blue Book, which was established to investigate UFO sightings.
witness description: Female, 18 years old, resides in Morrow, Ohio.
